{{<description>}}
I’ve been a fan of P.O.D. since the 90s, and I’ve continued to follow them throughout their career. This is a collection of my favorite tracks into a single playlist.
{{</description>}}

{{<fullimage src="https://cdn.ryanparman.com/hugo/posts/2019/pod@2x.jpg" alt="P.O.D.">}}

## Playlist

{{< apple-music "https://embed.music.apple.com/us/playlist/best-of-p-o-d/pl.u-ZPEorsrzbxm?app=music" "album" >}}

View on [Apple Music](https://beta.music.apple.com/us/playlist/best-of-p-o-d/pl.u-ZPEorsrzbxm), [Pandora](https://www.pandora.com/playlist/PL:1125899955795462:24885502), or [Spotify](https://open.spotify.com/user/skyzyx/playlist/3JAD0XdmvyNBqdF277CVvd?si=-na86339SpCZz5JITzxKSQ) (in varying degrees of completeness).

## A few notes…

For the most part, all of P.O.D.’s major-label releases (e.g., Atlantic, Universal) are easy to find across music services, but a couple of albums are _incredibly_ hard to find. My original, local version of the playlist includes copies of:

1. "Draw the Line" and "Full Color" from [The Warrior’s EP]({{< wayback "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Warriors_EP" >}}) (1998) on [Tooth & Nail records]({{< wayback "https://www.toothandnail.com" >}}). A copyright-infringed copy can be found on [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wxvbkVvNkDw&list=PLJhq8uea0Bmb5qzTVDLoacuPMFs3khDf_).

1. "Addicted", "Kaliforn-Eye-A", "End of the World", and "When Angels & Serpents Dance" from [When Angels & Serpents Dance]({{< wayback "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/When_Angels_%26_Serpents_Dance" >}}) (2008) on [INO Records]({{< wayback "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/INO_Records" >}}) and [Columbia Records]({{< wayback "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Columbia_Records" >}}). A copyright-infringed copy can be found on [YouTube](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=EAdab7Fnjzw&list=PLJhq8uea0BmbZrQdjXDKObO7l-y8QzYDk).
